\n<Benji>"Well, well, Lady Roselitte. Thank you for taking the

\n<Benji>"Does your presence mean that you will accept our request?"

\n<Benji>"...Now then, let's talk business. As I proposed earlier, in
exchange for borrowing Ameria-san for a little while, we
will offer you commercial supplies here at a discounted
price."

\n<Benji>"Without further ado, please take this. It's a token of our
gratitude for listening to our offer. Feel free to purchase
as much as you like."

\n<Roselitte>"...This is a big help. Replenishing supplies is literally a
lifeline, after all."

\n<Benji>"...Then, Lady Roselitte, please call on us again when you

we will provide you with supplies."

\n<Benji>"Well, I have a proposal for you, Lady Roselitte--...Please
don't make that face. It's a piece of good news."

\n<Benji>"Thanks to you, we've managed to strike a deal with a
skilled apothecary. If we provide the materials, they will
supply us with high-quality healing potions."

\n<Benji>"The materials are all quite rare, but with just one of
each, it seems we can produce a considerable amount. How
about you try looking for them?"

\n<Benji>"Here are the four materials. I'll give you a note with
them."
You've obtained the High-Quality Healing Potion Note!

\n<Materials note>Koyoru Forest / "Red-Brown Fruits", Hornus Cave / "Zoko

Jungle / "Gonkako Moss"

\n<Benji>"Once you've gathered all four, please leave them with me.
I'll pass them on to the apothecary."
\n<Benji>"...Then, I wish you good fortune in battle."

\n<Roselitte>"...Indeed, having high-quality potions would be a great
help. If we have the time, perhaps we should look for them."

\n<Villager>"...My son was only 8 years old. He was mischievous and I
had to scold him at times, but he was very kind and a good
boy."

\n<Refugee>"...Don't worry. I'm with you. Big bro will protect you,
okay?"

The man clasped his hands together in prayer, his hands
trembling slightly.

\n<Villager>"Amazing, isn't it? The graveyard ran out of space to bury
in just one day. We're planning to make another one
elsewhere because it's not enough."

\n<Villager>"...Digging so many graves at once, I hate it. It was the
same during the great war. Day after day, just digging
graves..."

\n<Villager>"I thought I could spend the rest of my short life
peacefully, but life doesn't always go so smoothly, does
it?"

\n<Villager>"The crops and livestock are mostly safe. It seems the
monsters prefer humans."

\n<Villager>"This town is quite large, isn't it? Even though it's far
from the city, trade is thriving and it's a comfortable
place to live."
\n<Villager>"...But it has become much quieter now."

\n<Villager>"You all... I was saved that time. I will never forget this
debt for as long as I live."

\n<Villager>"Oh, you're the ones from that time! ...Huh, have you
forgotten already? That's terrible, we met in the Nanu-Ma
Forest, didn't we?"

\n<Villager>"Thanks for helping my partner back then! Now, as a way of
saying thanks, I'm spreading word of your deeds around
town!"
\n<Child>"Thank you, Onee-chan! My leg doesn't hurt anymore!"

\n<Ameria>"I'm glad. If it starts to hurt again, make sure to call for
Onee-chan, okay?"

\n<Villager>"My child is nowhere to be found... They must be hiding
after being attacked by monsters... It has to be..."

\n<Villager>"Ah, you must be...! I heard from the soldiers. Lady
Roselitte and the medical practitioner saved our child..."

\n<Villager>"Thank you so very much. This isn't much, but please accept
it."

\n<Villager>"This must also be the guidance of the gods. I pray for both
of your safety."

\n<Villager>"This may also be the guidance of the gods. I pray for the
safety of you both."

\n<Refugee>"Thank you for saving me back then. I'm only here now thanks
to Ameria-chan."

\n<Child>"Big sis! I'll definitely become a medical practitioner just
like you!"
\n<Ameria>"Ehehe... Thank you! Let's work hard together, okay?"

\n<Refugee>"Ah, Lady Roselitte, Ameria-chan. I really don't know how to
thank you enough..."
Roselitte received the Necklace of Resistance.

\n<Refugee>"It was something my late mother gave me. But I think she
would be happier if you, Lady Roselitte, were to have it."

\n<Refugee>"Ameria-chan, once you've settled down, come visit again.
I'll properly thank you then. So hang in there."
\n<Ameria>"Yeah, thank you. I'll do my best!"
\n<Refugee>"Thank you so much for this time."

\n<Guard>"Thank you for your hard work. Please leave the town's
security to me!"
